{
  "texts": [
    "We consider the well-known CHB-MIT dataset and the novel PEDESITE dataset for these analyses.",
    "The Pedesite study takes place during routine clinical evaluations at the in-hospital epilepsy monitoring unit where patients are investigated in order to record and characterize their epileptic seizures.",
    "Before the start of the monitoring, scalp-EEG electrodes are fixed to the patient's scalp.",
    "Afterward, these electrodes are connected to an amplifier and then converted from analog to digital signals, which are then displayed in a software program, allowing healthcare professionals to monitor brain activity in real-time, coupled with the video, electrocardiogram, and pulse oximetry signals.",
    "Patient monitoring lasts from 2 consecutive days up to two weeks."
  ]
}